article.headline: Bowling Green 54, Wright St. 41
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- A'uston Calhoun led Bowling Green with 19 points and eight rebounds to lead the Falcons to a 54-41 victory over Wright State Monday night in a nonconference win. Calhoun was just 3-of-11 shooting but was a perfect 12 of 12 from the free-throw line, and finished the night 14 points shy of 1,000 for his career. The double-digit scoring performance was the 50th of his career. The teams were tied 22-all at halftime, and Wright State (5-3) led 34-31 with 12:23 left when Richaun Homes scored six straight points to spark a 13-0 Bowling Green (4-4) run. The Raiders missed 10 of their final 13 shots, including all five in the final 5 minutes. Jordon Crawford had three steals for the Falcons, giving him 145 for his career and moving him past Joe Moore (143) for 10th all-time at Bowling Green. Reggie Arceneaux led the Raiders (5-3) with 13 points.
